<?php
$inputString = 'johnny cash';
$helperBefore = $block->getHelperBefore();
?>

<ul>
    <li>This page uses helper methods that CAPITALIZE input.</li>
    <li>The three identical helper methods are modified by three different plugins.</li>
    <li>The plugin types are "before", "after", and "around".</li>
    <li>Each plugin wraps content in a lowercase tag, like (before)content(/before).</li>
</ul>

<?php
$pluginType = "\"before\"";
$output = $helperBefore->baseMethod($inputString);
?>

<b>Plugin type: </b> <?php echo $pluginType;?><br/>
<b>Input: </b> <?php echo $inputString;?><br/>
<b>Output: </b> <?php echo $output;?><br/>

<br/><p>The "before" plugin modified the input to the helper, so the tags became capitalized.</p>

<?php
$pluginType = "\"after\"";
$helperAfter = $block->getHelperAfter();
$output = $helperAfter->baseMethod($inputString);
?>

<b>Plugin type: </b> <?php echo $pluginType;?><br/>
<b>Input: </b> <?php echo $inputString;?><br/>
<b>Output: </b> <?php echo $output;?><br/>

<br/><p>The "after" plugin modified the output of the helper after it executed, so the tags did not become capitalized.</p>

<?php
$pluginType = "\"around\"";
$helperAround = $block->getHelperAround();
$output = $helperAround->baseMethod($inputString);
?>

<b>Plugin type: </b> <?php echo $pluginType;?><br/>
<b>Input: </b> <?php echo $inputString;?><br/>
<b>Output: </b> <?php echo $output;?><br/>

<br/><p>
    The "around" plugin modifies the input the the helper with one set of tags, then calls the helper, then modifies the output with the second set of tags.
</p>
